cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ED, cs.HC. 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to manipulate the difficulty of C-tests. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves predicting gap difficulty, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential use of these techniques in language assessment tests, which could fall under cs.ED (Education) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
